<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Seriena on 08-07-2001 11:52 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Wisecleric

I will agree that it doesn't take a lot of talent to kill the spiders in velks but I really do think they did a good job upgrading this zone. As for the spider drops, I think their right on par with what they should be. It's a high lvl dungeon, the gear should be equal or greater than what 50+ characters are wearing.


However, I really think that the pit rewards are lacking with respect to the risk involved. Like I said earlier, everything we got down there has gone to alts or to people to sell. Here's the drops we got last night off 3 named mobs all of which were red to me at lvl 55. Our group make up was 60 war, 60 rogue, 54 bard, 54 chanter, 55 druid, 52 cleric

1st mob (very easy to kill) = great divide portal spell, wakening land portal spell.

2nd mob (a bit tougher, came with an add and CH'd) = diamond and some book (can't recall the name) that was int caster only, primary or secondary melee +50 HP +45 mana. 

3rd mob (very hard and we almost lost this fight) = Mask ac5 +3 to all saves.

Now, who at lvl 51+ would use this stuff with the exception of the diamond? To me, that seems so off it's not even funny. Kill a lvl 58/59 mob and get a lvl 39 portal spell or a book with 50 hp's and 45 mana? Now, don't get me wrong, we did get quest gems, and spider fur cloaks off the other mobs we killed but it seems to me that they forgot to change some of the loot tables when they upgraded the zone from 40ish to 50ish.


Pick up groups in relationship with other dungeons (os, karnors etc). I've found most if not all of the pick up groups I've had in velks are waaaayyy better than any of the groups I've found in OS or karnors. It reminds me of the groups I had in CoM. Laid back, not in a rush to pull pull pull and no loot whores. I don't see OS becoming byog at all. On our server OS is so packed it's unreal


</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
